label: Life Stage (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The age class or life stage of the Organism(s) at the time the Occurrence was recorded.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Sampling Protocol (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The methods or protocols used during an Event, denoted by an IRI.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is describe an Event with no more than one sampling protocol. In the case of a summary Event in which a specific protocol can not be attributed to specific Occurrences, the recommended best practice is to repeat the property for each IRI that denotes a different sampling protocol that applies to the Occurrence.

label: Measurement Value (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Footprint SRS (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The ellipsoid, geodetic datum, or spatial reference system (SRS) upon which the geometry given in footprintWKT is based.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Georeference Verification Status (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description for the Location of the Occurrence.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Vertical Datum (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The vertical datum used as the reference upon which the values in the elevation terms are based.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.
